SIMPLE: horseman
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Horseman
<hw>Horse"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Horsemen</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A rider on
horseback; one skilled in the management of horses; a mounted
man.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A mounted soldier; a
cavalryman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A land crab of the
genus <gen>Ocypoda</gen>, living on the coast of Brazil and the West
Indies, noted for running very swiftly.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A West
Indian fish of the genus <gen>Eques</gen>, as the light-horseman
(<spn>Eques lanceolatus</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Horsemanship</ent>⟦br⟧
